{
  "texts": [
    "Small problems.",
    "We start with the small problem used in the previous section, with n = 74 assets, and without a factor risk model.",
    "Figure 4 shows the time required for each of the 4,436 days in the back-test, broken down into updating and logging (shown in green), CVXPY overhead (shown in blue, negligible), and solver time, the time required to solve the resulting cone program.",
    "(We do not count factorizing the covariance matrix, or computing the mean forecasts, since these are done ahead of time, and the time is amortized across all back-tests.)",
    "The 17 year back-test, which involve solving 4,436 problems, takes around 104 seconds on a MacBook Pro with an M1 Pro processor, or about 23ms per day on average."
  ]
}